The Quiet Woods

The quiet woods where shadows dwell,
And whispers wake the trees;
With Nature's song and silence fell,
In harmony and ease.
The brook that wanders, soft and slow,
Reflects the azure sky,
And in such peace, the heart will glow,
As time does flutter by.

- John Clare
